    "section": "314.4",
    "title": "parallels Section 313.1, Exception 2 (see commentary, Section 313.1)",
    "chapter": 3,
    "chapterTitle": "General Requirements",
    "body": [
      "314.4 parallels Section 313.1, Exception 2 (see commentary, Section 313.1). New electric and hybrid vehicles have tradi-tional 12V ignition batteries and main batteries for propulsion. This section clarifies in Item 1 that the ignition batteries should be disconnected. The main batteries of these vehicles are typically disconnected when the vehicle ignition batteries are disconnected. Item 2 includes criteria for alternative fuels, requiring that the tanks for each type do not exceed the amounts listed rather than requiring that these vehicles have to completely purge all fuel out of their tanks when they are located at indoor displays. Purging could allow oxygen to enter the tank which, when refueled, may create an explosive atmosphere. In addition, for composite tanks, the liner may be damaged if the internal pressure is reduced to zero. This item specifies the quantities allowed for each alternative fuel with the energy equivalent of 5 gallons of Class 1 liquid fuel (gasoline).",
      "GENERAL REQUIREMENTS",
      "SECTION 315—GENERAL STORAGE",
      "General. Storage shall be in accordance with Sections 315.2 through 315.6. Outdoor pallet storage shall be in accordance with Sections 315.2 and 315.7.",
      "Exception: Wood and wood composite pallets stored outdoors at pallet manufacturing and recycling facilities and complying with Section 2810."
    ],
